  <thing id="cBHDMark1" name="Mark (1)" description="Mark (Ex): A bloodhound can target, or mark, an individual humanoid or monstrous humanoid foe to better hunt that enemy. To do so, the bloodhound must focus on a foe who is present and visible, or on the depiction or description of one who is not, for 10 minutes. Any interruption ruins the attempt and forces the bloodhound to start the process again. Once this study is complete, that target is called a mark. \n\nA bloodhound adds his bloodhound level as an insight bonus on all Gather Information, Listen, Search, Spot, and Survival checks made to determine the whereabouts of a mark. As a bloodhound gains levels, he gains additional abilities that can be used against a mark. \n\nIf a bloodhound chooses a new mark before apprehending an existing one, the latter becomes unmarked, and the bloodhound loses experience points equal to the amount he would have earned for defeating that creature. A bloodhound can choose a mark only once a week. \n\nInitially, a bloodhound can have only one mark at a time. For every three bloodhound levels gained beyond 1st, a bloodhound can have one additional mark, but only if all the marks are chosen during the same process (see above). For example, a 4th-level bloodhound could mark two bugbears in the same group of prisoners, or the depictions of a bugbear and a hobgoblin if both were studied at the same time. If a bloodhound gives up on apprehending any of his marks, all remaining marked creatures become unmarked as described above." compset="ClSpecial">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpBHD"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xMark"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="10000"><![CDATA[if (field[xTotalLev].value >= 1) then
   hero.child[xMark].field[Value].value += 1
   hero.child[xMark].field[hTotal].value += 1   
endif
if (field[xTotalLev].value >= 4) then
   hero.child[xMark].field[Value].value += 1
   hero.child[xMark].field[hTotal].value += 1 
endif
if (field[xTotalLev].value >= 7) then
   hero.child[xMark].field[Value].value += 1
   hero.child[xMark].field[hTotal].value += 1 
endif
if (field[xTotalLev].value >= 10) then
   hero.child[xMark].field[Value].value += 1
   hero.child[xMark].field[hTotal].value += 1 
endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
