  <thing id="wLongaxe" name="Longaxe" description="If you are proficient with the longaxe, you can treat it as a reach weapon any time you use the Power Attack feat to shift 3 or more points of your attack bonus from attack to damage.\n\nWhen you use a longaxe in this manner you can strike opponents 10 feet away, but you cannot use it against an adjacent foe. Because you determine the use of the power attack feat for an entire turn, you must wield the longaxe as either a reach weapon or a normal weapon until the beginning of your next turn once you make the decision. You cannot wield it as both a reach weapon and a normal weapon in the same turn.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Adventurer" compset="Weapon">
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="15"/>
    <fieldval field="gSizeCost" value="35"/>
    <usesource source="CompAdvent"/>
