  <thing id="cSpTSnAtt" name="Sneak Attack +1d6" description="A spellthief deals an extra 1d6 points of damage when flanking an opponent or at any time when the target would be denied its Dexterity bonus. This extra damage applies to ranged attacks only if the target is within 30 feet. It increases to 2d6 points at 5th level, 3d6 points at 9th level, 4d6 points at 13th level, and 5d6 points at 17th level. See the rogue class feature, page 50 of the Player&apos;s Handbook. If a spellthief gets a sneak attack bonus from another source (such as rogue levels), the bonuses on damage stack." compset="ClSpecial">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1" name="1" abbrev="1"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp" name="SpecUp" abbrev="SpecUp"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpT"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack" name="Attack" abbrev="Attack"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xSneakAtt"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      ~ Add our level / 4 to our sneak attack damage and round up.
      var sneak as number
      sneak = field[xTotalLev].value / 4
      sneak = round(sneak, 0, 1)

      hero.child[xSneakAtt].field[Value].value += sneak
      field[livename].text = "Sneak Attack +" & sneak & "d6"
      field[xSumm].text = "+" & sneak & "d6 to your Sneak Attack damage."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSpTSteSpl" name="Steal Spell" description="A spellthief can siphon spell energy away from his target and use it himself. A spellthief who hits an opponent with a successful sneak attack can choose to forgo dealing 1d6 points of sneak attack damage and instead steal a spell, or the potential to cast a specific known spell, from his target. If the target is willing, a spellthief can steal a spell with a touch as a standard action.\n\nThe target of a steal spell attack loses one 0 or 1st-level spell from memory if she prepares spells ahead of time, or one 0 or 1st-level spell slot if she is a spontaneous caster. A spontaneous caster also loses the ability to cast the stolen spell for 1 minute. If the target has no spells prepared (or has no remaining spell slots), this ability has no effect. A spellthief can choose which spell to steal; otherwise, the DM determines the stolen spell randomly. If a spellthief tries to steal a spell that isn&apos;t available, the stolen spell (or spell slot) is determined randomly from among those the target has available.\n\nFor example, a 1st-level spellthief who uses this ability against a 1st-level sorcerer could choose to steal {i}magic missile{/i}. Assuming the sorcerer knew that spell, a successful steal spell attack would eliminate one 1st-level spell slot and temporarily prevent her from casting {i}magic missile{/i}. If the same spellthief stole {i}magic missile{/i} from a wizard who had it prepared, the wizard would lose one prepared {i}magic missile{/i} spell (but wouldn&apos;t lose any other {i}magic missile{/i} spells she might also have prepared).\n\nAfter stealing a spell, a spellthief can cast the spell himself on a subsequent turn. Treat the spell as if it were cast by the original owner of the spell for the purpose of determining caster level, save DC, and so forth. A spellthief can cast this spell even if he doesn&apos;t have the minimum ability score normally required to cast a spell of that level. The spellthief must supply the same components (including verbal, somatic, material, XP, and any focus) required for the stolen spell. Alternatively, a spellthief of 4th level or higher can use the stolen spell power to cast any spellthief spell that he knows of the same level or lower (effectively, this gives the spellthief one free casting of a known spell). A spellthief must cast a stolen spell (or use its energy to cast one of his own spells) within 1 hour of stealing it; otherwise, the extra spell energy fades harmlessly away.\n\nAt 4th level, he can steal spells of up to 2nd level, and for every two levels gained after 4th, the maximum spell level stolen increases by one (up to a maximum of 9th-level spells at 18th level).\n\nAt any one time, a spellthief can possess a maximum number of stolen spell levels equal to his class level (treat 0-level spells as 1/2 level for this purpose). For instance, a 4th-level spellthief can have two stolen 2nd-level spells, or one 2nd-level spell and two 1st-level spells. If he steals a spell that would cause him to exceed this limit, he must choose to lose stolen spells sufficient to reduce his total number of stolen spell levels to no more than his maximum.\n\nA spellthief can&apos;t apply metamagic feats or other effects to the stolen spell unless the specific spell stolen was prepared with such an effect. For example, a spellthief of 6th level or higher could steal a wizard&apos;s empowered {i}magic missile{/i}, but only if he specifically chose to steal empowered {i}magic missile{/i}. If he chose to steal an unmodified {i}magic missile{/i}, he couldn&apos;t steal an empowered {i}magic missile{/i}, a silent {i}magic missile{/i}, or any other metamagic form of the spell. A spellthief couldn&apos;t steal an empowered {i}magic missile{/i} from a sorcerer, since the sorcerer applies metamagic effects upon casting and thus has no prepared empowered {i}magic missile{/i} spell.\n\nThis ability works only against spells. It has no effect on psionic powers or spell-like abilities." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Sneak att -1d6, steal spell to cast as owner or use for spellthief spell.">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpT"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xSpellEner"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[      ~ Max spell level is class level / 2, rounded down
      var spellevel as number
      spellevel = field[xTotalLev].value / 2
      spellevel = round(spellevel, 0, -1)

      ~ Minimum is 1, maximum is 9
      if (spellevel < 1) then
         spellevel = 1
      elseif (spellevel > 9) then
         spellevel = 9
      endif

      ~ Set our name
      if (spellevel = 1) then
        field[livename].text = "Steal Spell (0-" & spellevel & "st)"
      elseif (spellevel = 2) then
        field[livename].text = "Steal Spell (0-" & spellevel & "nd)"
      elseif (spellevel = 3) then
        field[livename].text = "Steal Spell (0-" & spellevel & "rd)"
      else
        field[livename].text = "Steal Spell (0-" & spellevel & "th)"
      endif

      ~ Set the charges for the Spell energy.
      hero.childfound[xSpellEner].field[hTotal].value = field[xTotalLev].value]]></eval>
    </thing>
