  <thing id="cSpTDetMag" name="{i}Detect Magic{/i}" description="A spellthief of 2nd level or higher can use {i}detect magic{/i} a number of times per day equal to his Charisma bonus, if any (minimum 1). His caster level is equal to his spellthief class level." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Use {i}detect magic{/i} as a spell like ability X times a day (CL X).">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpT"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="2"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Sense"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[   var uses as number
   uses = hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
     if (uses < 1) then
      uses = 1
     endif

   var castlev as number
   castlev = field[xTotalLev].value

   field[xSumm].text = "Use {i}detect magic{/i} as a spell like ability " & uses & " times a day (CL" & castlev & ")."
   field[hTotal].value = uses]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSpTSplGra" name="Spellgrace" description="A spellthief of 2nd level or higher gains a +1 competence bonus on his saves against spells. This bonus improves to +2 at 11th level and to +3 at 20th level." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Gain listed competence bonus on saves vs spells.">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpT"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="2"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Defense"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      ~ Get our level.
      var level as number
      level = field[xTotalLev].value

      ~ Set the bonus
      var bonus as number
       if (level >= 20) then
         bonus = 3
       elseif (level >= 11) then
         bonus = 2
       elseif (level >= 1) then
         bonus = 1
       endif

      field[livename].text = "Spellgrace +" & bonus & ""]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSpTStSpEf" name="Steal Spell Effect" description="Beginning at 2nd level, a spellthief can siphon an active spell effect from another creature. A spellthief who hits an opponent with a sneak attack can choose to forgo dealing 1d6 points of sneak attack damage and instead gain the effect of a single spell affecting the target. If the target is willing, a spellthief can steal a spell effect with a touch as a standard action.\n\nThe spellthief can choose which spell effect to steal; otherwise, the DM determines the stolen spell effect randomly. If a spellthief tries to steal a spell effect that isn&apos;t present, the stolen spell effect is determined randomly from among those currently in effect on the target. A spellthief can&apos;t steal a spell effect if its caster level exceeds his class level + his Charisma modifier.\n\nUpon stealing a spell effect, a spellthief gains the stolen effect (and the original creature loses that effect) for 1 minute per class level (or until the spell&apos;s duration expires, whichever comes first). If the spell effect&apos;s duration hasn&apos;t expired by this time, the spell effect returns to the creature that originally benefited from it.\n\nA spellthief can steal the effect of a spell only if the spell could be cast on him by the original caster. For example, a spellthief couldn&apos;t gain the effect of an {i}animal growth{/i} spell (unless the spellthief is of the animal type) or the effect of a {i}shield{/i} spell (since that spell&apos;s range is personal). If a spellthief tries to steal the effect of a spell not allowed to him, the effect is still suppressed on the original target of the spell for 1 minute per spellthief class level.\n\nThis ability does not work on spell effects that are immune to {i}dispel magic{/i} (such as {i}bestow curse{/i})." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Sneak att -1d6, steal effect (max CL XX) that caster could have cast on him.">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpT"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="2"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[    var castlev as number
    castlev = field[xTotalLev].value + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
        field[xSumm].text = "Sneak att -1d6, steal effect (max CL" & castlev & ") that caster could have cast on him."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSpTStEnRe" name="Steal Energy Resistance" description="Beginning at 3rd level, a spellthief can siphon off some or all of a target&apos;s resistance to an energy type (acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic). A spellthief who hits an opponent with a successful sneak attack can choose to forgo dealing 1d6 points of sneak attack damage and instead temporarily gain resistance 10 to an energy type to which his target is resistant (or immune). If the target is willing, a spellthief can steal energy resistance with a touch as a standard action.\n\nSimultaneously, the target creature&apos;s resistance to that energy type is reduced by 10 (to a minimum of 0). A creature with immunity to an energy type retains that immunity.\n\nIf his target has more than one type of resistance to energy, a spellthief can choose which kind to steal; otherwise, the DM determines the stolen resistance randomly from among those possessed by the target. If a spellthief chooses to steal a type of resistance that the target doesn&apos;t possess, the stolen type of resistance is determined randomly from those possessed by the target.\n\nThe resistance a spellthief gains from using this ability lasts for 1 minute. If the resistance is derived from a temporary effect (such as a spell), the stolen resistance disappears when the effect expires.\n\nA spellthief can use this ability multiple times, but its effects do not stack unless they apply to different types of energy. For example, throughout a long combat, a spellthief might use this ability to gain resistance to fire and resistance to cold, but he could not use it twice on a creature that is resistant to fire to gain twice as much resistance to fire (nor to reduce the creature&apos;s resistance to fire by twice as much).\n\nAt 11th level, a spellthief can steal resistance 20 to an energy type by using this ability, and at 19th level he can steal resistance 30 to an energy type." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Sneak att -1d6, lower foe&apos;s energy resist (immunity remains), gain same amt.">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpT"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="3"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[   var level as number
   level = field[xTotalLev].value

   var resist as number
     if (level >= 19) then
       resist = 30
     elseif (level >= 11) then
       resist = 20
     else
       resist = 10
     endif

   field[livename].text = "Steal Energy Resistance " & resist & ""]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSpTStSLAb" name="Steal Spell-Like Ability" description="At 5th level and higher, a spellthief can use a sneak attack to temporarily steal a creature&apos;s spell-like ability. A spellthief who hits an opponent with a sneak attack can choose to forgo dealing 1d6 points of sneak attack damage and instead gain one use of one of the target&apos;s spell-like abilities. If the target is willing, a spellthief can steal a spell-like ability with a touch as a standard action.\n\nThis spell-like ability can originate from the target&apos;s class, race, template, or any other source, and can be of any level up to a maximum of one-third the spellthief&apos;s class level. A spellthief can select a specific spell-like ability to steal; otherwise, the DM chooses the ability at random. If the ability has a limited number of uses per day, the target must have at least one such use left, or the spellthief can&apos;t steal the ability. If the target can&apos;t use its ability at the present time (such as a summoned demon&apos;s summon ability), the spellthief can&apos;t steal it.\n\nA spellthief can use a stolen spell-like ability once. For all purposes (caster level, save DC, and so on), treat the spell-like ability as if it were being used by the original possessor of the ability. A spellthief must use the stolen spell-like ability within 1 minute of acquiring it, or it is lost harmlessly. Until the spellthief uses the ability (or until the minute elapses), the target cannot use the stolen ability." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Sneak att -1d6, gain use of an unspent SLA, unavailable to foe while you have.">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpT"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="5"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      ~ Max SLA level is class level / 3, rounded down.
      var SLAlev as number
      SLAlev = field[xTotalLev].value / 3
      SLAlev = round(SLAlev, 0, -1)

      ~ Minimum 1, maximum 9
      if (SLAlev < 1) then
         SLAlev = 1
      elseif (SLAlev > 9) then
         SLAlev = 9
      endif

      ~ Set name and summary.
      if (SLAlev = 1) then
        field[livename].text = "Steal Spell-Like Ability (0-" & SLAlev & "st)"
      elseif (SLAlev = 2) then
        field[livename].text = "Steal Spell-Like Ability (0-" & SLAlev & "nd)"
      elseif (SLAlev = 3) then
        field[livename].text = "Steal Spell-Like Ability (0-" & SLAlev & "rd)"
      else
        field[livename].text = "Steal Spell-Like Ability (0-" & SLAlev & "th)"
      endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSpTAbsSpl" name="Absorb Spell" description="Beginning at 7th level, if a spellthief makes a successful save against a spell that targets him, he can attempt to absorb the spell energy for later use. This ability affects only spells that have the spellthief as a target, not effect or area spells. A spellthief can&apos;t absorb a spell of a higher spell level than he could steal with his steal spell ability (see above).\n\nTo absorb a spell that targets him, a spellthief must succeed on a level check (1d20 + spellthief class level) against a DC of 10 + the spell&apos;s caster level. Failure indicates that the spell has its normal effect. Success means that the spellthief suffers no effect from the spell and can cast the spell later (or use its energy to cast one of his own spells known) as if he had stolen the spell with his steal spell ability. His normal limit of total spell levels stolen still applies.\n\nAt 20th level or higher, a spellthief can choose to use the stolen spell energy as an immediate action (Complete Adventurer pg 137), either to recast the original spell or to cast one of his own spells known using the stolen spell energy." compset="ClSpecial" summary="If save vs targetted spell, can make level check to absorb for later use.">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpT"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="7"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Defense"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[      ~ Max spell level is class level / 2, rounded down
      var spellevel as number
      spellevel = field[xTotalLev].value / 2
      spellevel = round(spellevel, 0, -1)

      ~ Minimum is 1, maximum is 9
      if (spellevel < 1) then
         spellevel = 1
      elseif (spellevel > 9) then
         spellevel = 9
      endif

      ~ Set our name
      if (spellevel = 1) then
        field[livename].text = "Absorb Spell (0-" & spellevel & "st)"
      elseif (spellevel = 2) then
        field[livename].text = "Absorb Spell (0-" & spellevel & "nd)"
      elseif (spellevel = 3) then
        field[livename].text = "Absorb Spell (0-" & spellevel & "rd)"
      elseif (field[xTotalLev].value >= 20) then
        field[livename].text = "Absorb Spell, Immediate (0-" & spellevel & "th)"
      else
        field[livename].text = "Absorb Spell (0-" & spellevel & "th)"
      endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSptArcSig" name="{i}Arcane Sight{/i}" description="Beginning at 9th level, a spellthief can use {i}arcane sight{/i} as a swift action (Complete Adventurer pg 137) a number of times per day equal to his Charisma modifier (minimum 1). His caster level is equal to his spellthief class level." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Swift, use {i}arcane sight{/i} as a spell like ability X times a day (CL X).">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="9"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Sense"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpT"/>
